# Electrolyzer

The electrolyzer splits water vapor and processes specialty gases for atmospherics workflows.

## Purpose
- Converts gases into useful outputs for station industry and advanced setups.
- Supports atmos/chemistry chains that depend on processed gas products.

## Operation
- Feed the machine with appropriate input gas.
- Keep it powered and connected to your pipe network.
- Route outputs to storage or downstream processing.

## Practical Tips
- Isolate the machine with dedicated piping to avoid contamination.
- Add analyzers/sensors for pressure and composition checks.
- Buffer output in tanks before feeding sensitive systems.
